---
import FAQCard from "./FAQCard.astro";
---

<section class="flex justify-center bg-xdark-purple shadow-[inset_0_16px_rgba(0,0,0,0.3)]">
  <div class="flex max-w-5xl grow flex-col gap-12 px-4 py-24 text-center text-2xl">
    <div>
      <p class="text-6xl drop-shadow-[0_0_8px_#FF5DA9]">FAQ</p>
      <p class="text-3xl drop-shadow-[0_0_4px_#FF5DA9]">
        You got questions? We got answers :D
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <FAQCard question="Am I eligible?" cardId={0}>
        Anyone 13–18 years old is welcome! If you’re just outside that range, please email
        us at <a class="underline" href="mailto:team@apohacks.com">team@apohacks.com</a>.
        If you’ve graduated high school, you’re welcome to volunteer; email us! Official
        ID with your birth date will be required at check-in.
      </FAQCard>

      <FAQCard question="Is this free?" cardId={1}>
        100%, thanks to sponsors. We’ll have meals, snacks, and beverages free of charge.
        <a class="underline" href="mailto:team@apohacks.com">Email us</a> if you’re
        interested in sponsoring—we'd love your support!
      </FAQCard>

      <FAQCard question="Where exactly is this event?" cardId={2}>
        We’re planning to host it in downtown Toronto and are contacting all sorts of
        companies to see who can host! Do you want to loan your office, or know someone
        who may be interested? <a class="underline" href="mailto:team@apohacks.com"
          >Email us</a
        >!
      </FAQCard>

      <FAQCard question="I’m new to coding, can I join?" cardId={3}>
        Apocalypse is for hackers of all skill levels. We’ll learn more together at
        workshops! If you want to start learning from home, YouTube and <a
          class="underline"
          href="https://workshops.hackclub.com/">these workshops</a
        >
         are awesome. If nothing else, you can learn surprisingly fast at a hackathon :)
      </FAQCard>

      <FAQCard question="Do I need a team?" cardId={4}>
        Not required, but highly encouraged! You can meet teammates at Apocalypse, too :)
      </FAQCard>

      <FAQCard question="What should I bring?" cardId={5}>
        Please bring your official ID, your laptop ⚡ <span class="font-bold"
          >with a charger</span
        > ⚡, a sleeping bag, toiletries, and an open mind.
      </FAQCard>

      <FAQCard
        question="My parents are worried—what should I do?"
        answer="Beginners and experienced makers alike are welcome!"
        cardId={6}
      >
        Apocalypse will have 24/7 supervision by background-checked adults, with venue
        access limited to participants. Please reach out to <a
          class="underline"
          href="mailto:team@apohacks.com">team@apohacks.com</a
        > with any concerns.
      </FAQCard>

      <FAQCard question="Who’s running this?" cardId={7}>
        We’re an eclectic group of teens who’ve worked on hackathons of all sizes, across
        the world. You may have attended AngelHacks Toronto or Haunted House Toronto—we
        ran those! Have any questions for us? Reach out at <a
          class="underline"
          href="mailto:team@apohacks.com">team@apohacks.com</a
        > and we’ll get back to you as soon as possible!
      </FAQCard>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

